What will the result be of the following expression?
```csharp
bool a = false;
bool b = true;
Console.WriteLine(a && b);
```

Consider the incomplete code:
```csharp
int x = 5;
// How do you increment the value of x by 1 here?
Console.WriteLine("Value of x = " + x.ToString());
```
Which of the following are valid ways to increment `x`?

What will the following code print?
```csharp
char letter = 'A'; 
Console.WriteLine(char.ToLower(letter));
```

What exception will be thrown when you try to divide an integer by 0?
```csharp
